<h3>Source archive</h3>
You can download the latest source archive from
<a href='http://tamacom.com/global/global-@VERSION@.tar.gz'>global-@VERSION@.tar.gz</a>
or
<a href='ftp://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu/global/'>GNU ftp site</a>.
<blockquote>
The archive files in GNU ftp site are signed by Shigio YAMAGUCHI, the release manager
of GNU GLOBAL. Here is
<a href='http://savannah.gnu.org/users/shigio'>Shigio's PGP public key (GPG Key)</a>.
</blockquote>

<h3>Binary archive</h3>

GNU GLOBAL project only distributes source package, and GNU GLOBAL only supports
UNIX(POSIX) environment.
Following packages are due to outside projects.
<p>
<a href='http://adoxa.3eeweb.com/global/index.html'>DOS and Windows 32 version</a>
are distributed by Jason Hood.
